{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-13939/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-13939"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:39:39"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman smiles as a man speaks to her."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-13939","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-13939"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1/742dff7e-6ae9-47ee-83cd-52b048634d0f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T14:49:31.034Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Strapless dresses proved a controversial topic on the film’s set: “During a fitting with [Vicky] Krieps, [costume designer] Bridges let it slip that he really wanted to design a strapless gown. It fit with the period, he told her, but [Daniel] Day-Lewis wasn’t into the idea. ‘I really felt the film was missing a strapless gown, because that was so typical in that period,’ says Bridges. ‘It could really have a great foundation and be very controlled, but still have the allure of the bare shoulders,’ he explains. Krieps revealed she thought the same thing, until Day-Lewis corrected her: Only Alma could elevate a strapless dress to something more refined. (‘Not on you,’ Day-Lewis told his co-star, according to Bridges)” (Harris, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW232389035 BCX2\" href=\"https://www.vulture.com/2018/01/the-story-behind-phantom-threads-majestic-couture-dresses.html\"><u>The Story Behind Phantom Thread’s Incredible Couture Dresses</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13939/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:378.70129870129864,119.99999999999989,1054.2857142857144,929.6103896103897"}}}]}]}]}